Reference: f = theta_0 + theta_1*numpy.log(d_tsi) + theta_2*d_W + theta_3*d_M + theta_4*d_S + theta_4*numpy.log(d_tsi)*d_W + theta_6*numpy.log(d_tsi)*d_M + theta_7*numpy.log(d_tsi)*d_S
f gives the value of the logit function
The variables d_W d_M and d_S are equal to 1.0 when the ith observation is for wooden masonry or steel structures respectively. They are equal to 0.0 in any other case.
